Graphical tasks

This next tasks are going to ask you to make a series of figures. For each one, I would like you to make all of them look good. Change the theme around, change the axis labels, etc. Additionally, each of these will use the reg column which has 2 factors. Change the color and/or shape of them both.

Task 1: Continuous vs.continuous plot

Create two scatterplots of logbodysize vs.trophic_position grouped by reg

First plot:
  • a 2 trend lines (method = lm), one for each reg variable
#plot 1.1
ggplot(data=bloom_df, aes(x=trophic_position, y=logbodysize, color = genus, pch = reg), group_by(reg)) + geom_point(method = lm) + ggtitle('Log Body Size vs. Trophic Group') + xlab('Tropic Position') + ylab('Log Body Size') + theme_bw() + stat_smooth(method='lm',linetype='dashed',colour='black',linewidth=2) + theme_classic()
## Warning in geom_point(method = lm): Ignoring unknown parameters: `method`
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Second plot
  • a single trend line for the whole model
#plot 1.2
ggplot(data=bloom_df, aes(x=trophic_position, y=logbodysize, color = genus)) + geom_point(method = lm) + ggtitle('Log Body Size vs. Trophic Group') + xlab('Tropic Position') + ylab('Log Body Size') + theme_bw() +  stat_smooth(method = 'lm', linetype='dashed',colour='black',linewidth=2)

Task 2: Continuous vs.categorical

The layout will be:
  • 2 panels: trophic_position and logbodysize
  • x axis: reg
  • y axis: value of trophic_position and logbodysize
Create 4 plots:
  • bar and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)
  • point and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)
  • box plots
  • raw data + point and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)

All these plots should have the same general layout but change the type of plot to visualize the data.

HINT: logbodysize and trophic_position need to be turned into long format

Example layout:

sample layout for task2

body_sum_df <- bloom_df %>%
  group_by(reg) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(logbodysize, na.rm = TRUE), #temp mean
            sd = sd(logbodysize, na.rm = TRUE), #temp standard deviation
            n = n()) %>% #temp count
  mutate(se = sd / sqrt(n), #Temp standard error
         ci = 1.96 * se) #Temp 95% confidence interval

view(body_sum_df)
body_sum_df$Measure <- 'Log Body Size'
view(body_sum_df)


troph_sum_df <- bloom_df %>%
  group_by(reg) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(trophic_position, na.rm = TRUE), #Ppt mean
            sd = sd(trophic_position, na.rm = TRUE), #Ppt standard deviation
            n = n()) %>% #Ppt count
  mutate(se = sd / sqrt(n), #Ppt standard error
         ci = 1.96*se) #Ppt 95% confidence interval
view(troph_sum_df)
troph_sum_df$Measure <- 'Trophic Position'
view(troph_sum_df)

bloom_sum_df2 <- rbind(body_sum_df,troph_sum_df)
view(bloom_sum_df2)

#plot 2.1

ggplot(data=bloom_sum_df2,aes(x=reg,y=mean,fill=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') + geom_bar(stat='identity') + theme_bw() +xlab('Water Adaptation') + geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - ci, ymax = mean + ci)) + ylab('Mean') + ggtitle('Trophic Position and Body Size by Water Adaptation Type')

#plot 2.2
ggplot(data=bloom_sum_df2,aes(x=reg,y=mean,color=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') + geom_point(stat='identity') + theme_bw() +xlab('Water Adaptation') + geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - ci, ymax = mean + ci)) + ylab('Mean') + ggtitle('Trophic Position and Body Size by Water Adaptation Type')

bloom_long_df <- bloom_df %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(logbodysize, trophic_position), names_to = "Measure", values_to = "Value")
view(bloom_long_df)
#plot 2.3
ggplot(data=bloom_long_df,aes(x=reg,y=Value,fill=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') +
  geom_boxplot()

#plot 2.4
ggplot(data=bloom_long_df,aes(x=reg,y=Value,color=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') +
  geom_point(size=2) +
  stat_summary(fun.data = mean_cl_boot, geom = "errorbar",color="black") + 
  stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = "point",size=5,colour="black") + theme_bw() +xlab("Water Adaptation") + ylab('Mean') + ggtitle('Trophic Position and Body Size by Water Adaptation Type')

Task 3: layering your plots

Make any two figures with the bloom_df! Can be something weve done or something completely different. Make one TERRIBLE figure and one GREAT figure.

Put them together using patchwork or ggarrange

#plot 3
bad_plot <- ggplot(data=bloom_long_df,aes(x=reg,y=Value,fill=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') + geom_violin(draw_quantiles = 0.5) + 
  scale_fill_npg() + 
  ggtitle('bad') + 
  theme(legend.position='none',
        plot.title = element_text(size = 20, colour="black",face = "bold"))
bad_plot

good_plot <- ggplot(data=bloom_long_df,aes(x=reg,y=Value,colour=reg)) +
  facet_wrap(~Measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') +
  geom_sina(size=3) +
  stat_summary(fun.data = mean_cl_boot, geom = "errorbar",color='black') + 
  stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = "point",size=5,colour='black') + theme_bw() +xlab("Water Adaptation") + ylab('Mean') + ggtitle('Trophic Position and Body Size by Water Adaptation Type')
